entral axis","Apical ectodermal ridge maintains proximal-distal outgrowth","Apical ectodermal ridge establishes anterior-posterior pattern"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe developing limb bud contains two essential signalling centres:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eapical ectodermal ridge\u003C/strong\u003E (AER) is a specialised region of thickened ectoderm at the distal tip of the limb bud. It secretes fibroblast growth factors that maintain the underlying mesenchyme in a proliferative state, driving \u003Cstrong\u003Eproximal-distal outgrowth\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezone of polarizing activity\u003C/strong\u003E (ZPA) is located in the posterior mesenchyme and secretes sonic hedgehog protein to establish \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior-posterior patterning\u003C/strong\u003E, including digit identity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eapical ectodermal ridge controls digit identity\u003C/strong\u003E - This is controlled by the ZPA through sonic hedgehog signalling\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ezone of polarizing activity determines dorsal-ventral axis\u003C/strong\u003E - Dorsal-ventral patterning is controlled by other signals including Wnt7a from the dorsal ectoderm\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The apical ectodermal ridge secretes fibroblast growth factors that maintain proximal-distal limb bud outgrowth.","The zone of polarizing activity secretes sonic hedgehog protein to control anterior-posterior patterning.","These two signalling centres work together to coordinate proper limb development and patterning."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Lu P, Yu Y, Perdue Y, Werb Z. The apical ectodermal ridge is a timer for generating distal limb progenitors. Development. 2008 Apr;135(8):1395-405."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58309"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15931"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58309","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58309"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T09:45:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-22T09:45:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8622"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72839"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4931"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb4","name":"Musculoskeletal","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10